# Qualification captures are raw terminal output: PTY bytes, escape sequences
# and all. Git's text heuristics see enough of them as text to rewrite line
# endings, which silently changes the bytes a capture exists to preserve — a
# checkout then hashes differently from the manifest that recorded it, and the
# byte-identity claim contradicts itself. Store them verbatim.
raw/qualification/**/captures/** -text -diff
raw/qualification/**/transcripts/** -text -diff
